{"lemma":"زَيْنَةٌ","slug":"زَيْنَةٌ","root":"ز.#.ن","root_slug":"ز-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"زَيْنَةٌ","root":"زين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":19},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18543"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"embellishment, adornment, ornament, decoration, garnish, decor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dressing up, putting on makeup, grooming oneself, sprucing up, adorning oneself, primping"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clothes, attire, finery"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"toilette"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ziː.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18543","headword_ar":"زِينَةٌ","root":"zyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAnahu","text_ar":"زَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yutazay~anu bihi","text_ar":"مَا يُتَزَيَّنُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing with which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which, one is adorned, ornamented, decorated, decked, bedecked, garnished, embellished, beautified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"graced;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which, one adorns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any such thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any ornament, ornature, decoration, garnish, embellishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyAnN","text_ar":"زِيانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayonN","text_ar":"زَيْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, [which see above,] signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziynapN","text_ar":"زِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har p. 139:) accord. to El- Harállee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziynapN","text_ar":"زِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautifying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellishing, a thing by another thing; consisting of apparel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ornament of gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of jewels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gems,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aspect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seen"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the eye that does not reach to the interior of that which is adorned"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereby"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to Er-Rághib, its proper mean-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1280},{"kind":"text","text":"ing is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that does not disgrace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"render unseemly, a man, in any of his states"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conditions, either in the present world or in that which is to come:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but that which adorns him in one state or condition, exclusively of another, is in one point of view"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayonN","text_ar":"شَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": summarily speaking, it is of three kinds; namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mental, such as knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science, and good tenets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodily, such as strength, and tallness of stature, and beauty of aspect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extrinsic, such as wealth, and rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and all these are mentioned in the Kur: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyanN","text_ar":"زِيَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd in x. 25.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziynapu AlHayaApi Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"زِينَةُ الحَيَاةِ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziynapu Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"زِينَةُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ornature, finery, show, pomp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gaiety, of the present life"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"world;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] particularly includes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth and children."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kur xviii. 44.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziynapu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"زِينَةُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ornature of the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, of the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alz~iynapi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ الزِّينَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of ornature"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the festival"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiydu","text_ar":"العِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (S, K;) when men used [and still use] to adorn themselves with goodly articles of apparel. (TA.) And also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of the breaking"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the dam a little within the entrance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the canal of Misr"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the present capital of Egypt, El-Káhireh, which we call “ Cairo ”], (K, TA,) i. e. the canal which runs through the midst of Misr, and [the dam of] which is broken when the Nile has attained the height of sixteen cubits or more: this day is said to be meant in the Kur xx. 61: it is one of the days observed in Egypt with the greatest gladness and rejoicing from ancient times; and its observance in the days of the Fátimees was such as is inconceivable, as it is described in the “ Khitat ” of El-Makreezee. (TA. [The modern observances of this day, and of other days in relation to the rise of the Nile, are described in my work on the Modern Egyptians.])"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}